## 📊 Splunk Training & Certifications

Hands-on training completed using Splunk Enterprise, focused on Security Information and Event Management (SIEM), log analysis, and threat detection within a Security Operations Center (SOC) environment.

These certifications demonstrate practical experience with:

* Writing and optimizing SPL (Search Processing Language) queries
* Extracting, normalizing, and analyzing log data using fields
* Building and leveraging data models for structured event correlation
* Applying statistical analysis techniques to identify anomalies and suspicious activity
* Understanding SIEM workflows within Splunk Enterprise Security
* Supporting threat detection, alert triage, and incident investigation processes

Each course reinforces core Security+ (SY0-701) concepts, including:

* Security Operations
* Threat Detection & Analysis
* Log Monitoring and Event Correlation

The certificates linked below provide verification of completed training and foundational proficiency in Splunk-based security analysis.
